race.comment: BOSUN (2) is a five-year-old on debut, but only appeared at the trials for the first time in August. He's a half-brother to the handy Malkar Pindari who has placed at Listed level. He's shown good ability in his heats and this looks to shape to advantage on debut. ARTICOLE (6) is another on debut, this time for the Steele Casey barn. His latest outing was solid at Lark Hill and Pike's booking adds intrigue. Drawn perfectly and a bold showing is expected on debut. CASSENITE (8) settled last at Belmont first-up and flew home, beaten just 1L. Out to 1200m now is a big tick and if she can build on what she showed fresh, she'll be right in the thick of the action. LONG LAUGH (1) has been knocking on the door for a while now and can't be discounted despite a wide draw. GRACEFUL LASS (11) was solid on debut and is open to plenty of improvement now.
